# DJ Shorts Analyzer - Cursor AI Rules

## Project Structure
- Main repository: `/Users/terryberk/git/djshorts/analyzer`
- Wiki repository: `/Users/terryberk/git/djshorts/analyzer/wiki` (separate git repo)
- Wiki URL: https://github.com/dj-shorts/analyzer.wiki.git
- Public wiki: https://github.com/dj-shorts/analyzer/wiki

## Wiki Management
- Wiki is a separate git repository with its own .git folder
- Uses `master` branch as default (GitHub wiki requirement)
- To update wiki: `cd wiki/ && git add . && git commit -m "message" && git push origin master`
- Changes appear immediately on GitHub wiki page

## Documentation Strategy
- Main README.md: Streamlined (125 lines) with essential info and wiki links
- Wiki: Detailed documentation (10+ comprehensive guides)
- All detailed documentation moved from main README to wiki
- Cross-references: README links to specific wiki pages

## Wiki Files Structure
- Home.md - Main wiki page with documentation index
- Setup-Guide.md - Installation and configuration
- Docker-Guide.md - Docker usage and deployment
- Monitoring-Setup.md - Prometheus + Grafana setup
- CI-CD-Pipeline.md - CI/CD documentation
- Testing-Guide.md - Testing procedures
- TestSprite-Integration.md - Advanced testing
- Epic-Reports.md - Development progress
- Manual-Download-Migration.md - Manual download workflow
- README.md - Wiki-specific documentation

## Key Commands
- Docker: `docker run --rm -v $(pwd)/data:/data ghcr.io/dj-shorts/analyzer:latest python -m analyzer.cli /data/video.mp4 --clips 3`
- Local: `uv run analyzer video.mp4 --clips 6`
- Tests: `uv run pytest`
- Wiki update: `cd wiki/ && git add . && git commit -m "Update docs" && git push origin master`

## Important Notes
- Always use `python -m analyzer.cli` instead of `analyzer` command
- Docker commands use `config/Dockerfile` and `config/docker-compose.yml`
- Wiki should be updated when adding new features
- Keep main README.md concise and reference wiki for details
